gomodel:SYNGO_3652  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: RIM1/RIM2 knockout neurons display a reduction in action potential-induced presynaptic calcium influx (Figure 5). RIM1 acts by regulating the presynaptic localization of voltage-gated calcium channels (Figure 8), mediated by its PDZ domain (Figure 7). Due to their high homology, RIM1 and RIM2 are assumed to be redundant for this process.\n\n23/01/2017 Pim\n- effect on Ca influx show in Fig.5\n- effect on VGCC localization shown in Fig.8\n- effect on synaptic transmission shown in Fig.3. Experimental description: We cultured neurons from newborn conditional double KO mice and infected these neurons with lentiviruses expressing EGFP-tagged active or inactive cre-recombinases." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7620-2704" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1558-1958" ;
        dc:date           "2018-06-07" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_3652" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

